==Arabic alphabet==

===Letter===
'''{{ARchar|Ш§ / ЩҖШ§}}'''

# Althought usually considered to be the first letter of the [[Arabic]] alphabet, the small [[hamza]] ({{ARchar|[[ШЎ]]}}) that sit on top of {{ARchar|[[ШЈ]]}} is really the first letter of the Arabic alphabet, and the tall column is its bearer. This article only deals with the lower part, the bearer, which is called {{ARchar|[[Ш§Щ„ЩҒ]]}} (вҖҷГЎlif) and, without the hamza, is used to lengthen a preceding vowel, often [[a]]. It is followed by {{ARchar|[[ШЁ]]}}.

===Pronunciation===
'''Combined with [[fathah]]:'''
{{ARchar|[[п№¶Ш§]]}} вҖ” '''ДҒ'''.

'''Combined with [[kasra]]:'''
{{ARchar|[[п№әШ§]]}} вҖ” '''Д«'''.

'''Combined with [[damma]]:'''
{{ARchar|[[п№ёШ§]]}} вҖ” '''Е«'''.

